  "prompt": "Is Honey Singh from IIT-B?",
  "response": "No, Yo Yo Honey Singh is not from IIT Bombay (IIT-B). Honey Singh, whose real name is Hirdesh Singh, pursued his education in Chandigarh. He attended DAV College in Chandigarh before embarking on his career in music and entertainment. There is no public information or credible sources indicating that he attended IIT Bombay or any other Indian Institute of Technology.\n\nIf you have heard otherwise, it might be a case of mistaken identity or misinformation. Honey Singh is widely recognized for his contributions to the Indian music industry, particularly in the genres of hip-hop and pop, rather than for an academic association with IIT.",
